txt.en: Tyrant Uzulthrang is here for battle and only battle. Stationed outside of Tol Ascarnen, the Tyrant pledges that he will fight against the enemy if you prove that you are worthy of his notice.
'Keep the pass you maggots! I will wait for none!'

'I've no time for chatter or chittering. Listen well, as I've a temper built only for battle and I will not tolerate failure.

'I need proof that you are worthy of fighting along my side, [placeholder]. You are a lowly worm to me, and without proof, I will not assist you...my strength and standing are not for risking on such pitiful slugs like you.

'Bring me proof that you are a true combatant in the service of Mordirith, Angmar, and Lugbúrz, and I will join your assault against the enemy!'
Tyrant Uzulthrang told you to assemble proof of your deeds, then and only then will he assist you in destroying the fools within Tol Ascarnen. He did not, however, tell you what proof he requires.

'Let nothing ill be spoken of you this day, [placeholder]. I shall heed your call and storm the castle with you.

'We shall rise for the glory of Angmar!

'We shall rise for the favour of Lugbúrz!

'We shall die to see that Mordirith's Army does not fail!

'Come on, lads! Let us have fun storming the castle!'
'Get me what I need you worthless wretch. I will not fight alongside sluggards and maggots.'
'Well done, maggots! We've won the day!'
Return the items to Tyrant Uzulthrang
